<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-82-0956 </DOCNO><TEXT>In a nuclear reactor (BW heating reactor) with a liquid coolant whichis pressurized by a pump and is taken via a pipe with horizontal sectionsto hydraulically operated control rods, the horizontal sections are laidwith a slope of a few percent and are connected in series so that thereis a constant drop from the highest point of the pipe to the pump. Thismakes it possible to empty the pipe completely for maintenance work (dismantlingof the pressure vessel lid).</TEXT></DOC>